1
00:00:32,345 --> 00:00:36,057
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

2
00:00:36,140 --> 00:00:38,976
15 YEARS AGO

3
00:00:40,227 --> 00:00:41,854
EPISODE 3

4
00:00:51,864 --> 00:00:52,907
You can do it!

5
00:01:07,588 --> 00:01:08,756
Hey, that's enough.

6
00:01:11,676 --> 00:01:12,927
Hey, Chow Yun-fat.

7
00:01:13,844 --> 00:01:16,138
You're not even part of the Hwasan Sect.

8
00:01:16,222 --> 00:01:17,598
This is a fight between your betters

9
00:01:17,682 --> 00:01:21,143
so what the hell is your problem,
jumping in like that?

10
00:01:21,686 --> 00:01:23,479
You've done enough. Now get lost.

11
00:01:23,562 --> 00:01:24,980
You're the ones...

12
00:01:25,690 --> 00:01:27,775
who should get lost
while I'm still asking nicely.

13
00:01:28,901 --> 00:01:32,905
- Oh, yeah?
- He really thinks he's Chow Yun-fat.

14
00:01:33,989 --> 00:01:35,199
Hey, what are you all doing?

15
00:01:35,741 --> 00:01:36,951
Let's wrap this up.

16
00:01:48,838 --> 00:01:49,839
Yes, sir.

17
00:01:53,759 --> 00:01:55,636
Looks like there are
about a dozen of them.

18
00:01:58,931 --> 00:02:00,057
Don't worry.

19
00:02:01,058 --> 00:02:02,560
An hour? No way.

20
00:02:03,978 --> 00:02:04,979
Thirty minutes.

21
00:02:06,230 --> 00:02:08,107
I'll have this cleaned up
and be on my way in 30 minutes.

22
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:11,736
What the hell is this? Jeez.

23
00:02:17,992 --> 00:02:18,993
Hey.

24
00:02:19,869 --> 00:02:20,995
You a Chow Yun-fat fan too?

25
00:02:21,537 --> 00:02:22,830
Oh, yes.

26
00:02:23,581 --> 00:02:24,582
What's your name?

27
00:02:25,458 --> 00:02:26,667
It's Ma Gong-bok!

28
00:02:28,836 --> 00:02:29,837
Ma Gong-bok.

29
00:02:30,671 --> 00:02:31,672
Nice name.

30
00:02:32,089 --> 00:02:33,174
You like sashimi, right?

31
00:02:34,258 --> 00:02:35,259
Yes!

32
00:02:44,810 --> 00:02:46,228
Let's finish this up quick
and get out of here.

33
00:02:46,771 --> 00:02:48,606
I'll treat you to all the fresh
sashimi you can eat.

34
00:02:49,231 --> 00:02:50,232
Yes!

35
00:03:28,020 --> 00:03:33,526
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

36
00:03:45,871 --> 00:03:46,872
Boss!

37
00:03:47,081 --> 00:03:48,541
Let's wrap this up quick
and get out of here.

38
00:04:12,481 --> 00:04:14,275
What are you doing? Go stop him!

39
00:04:17,111 --> 00:04:18,237
Damn it!

40
00:04:25,452 --> 00:04:26,453
Long time no see!

41
00:04:32,918 --> 00:04:34,295
Boss...

42
00:04:34,378 --> 00:04:35,796
Boss!

43
00:04:48,350 --> 00:04:49,351
Jeez.

44
00:04:49,977 --> 00:04:52,313
Beom-ryong, your fists
are as strong as ever.

45
00:04:57,234 --> 00:04:59,153
But you look a little tired.

46
00:04:59,486 --> 00:05:00,654
I'm just getting a little sleepy.

47
00:05:01,947 --> 00:05:03,824
You can't be tired already.

48
00:05:04,450 --> 00:05:06,327
We have to go straight to round two!

49
00:05:26,263 --> 00:05:27,264
Get them!

50
00:05:35,898 --> 00:05:37,441
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

51
00:06:22,778 --> 00:06:24,863
Who are those guys fighting over there?

52
00:06:25,823 --> 00:06:27,324
Wait, that guy...

53
00:06:27,866 --> 00:06:29,410
He's Oldboy, our regular.

54
00:06:30,119 --> 00:06:31,453
What's he doing here?

55
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:37,626
The young one is the motorcycle owner.

56
00:06:38,127 --> 00:06:39,545
And the other one...

57
00:06:41,046 --> 00:06:42,297
That's Bulgae.

58
00:07:45,027 --> 00:07:46,028
Stomp him!

59
00:07:50,824 --> 00:07:51,825
No.

60
00:07:56,789 --> 00:07:59,041
Stop!

61
00:08:11,762 --> 00:08:13,263
It's all my fault.

62
00:08:13,347 --> 00:08:15,766
Oh, Gong-bok. You stubborn bastard.

63
00:08:16,266 --> 00:08:18,811
After your boss got his ass kicked,
you're finally ready to talk?

64
00:08:19,269 --> 00:08:20,270
Fine, spit it out.

65
00:08:20,354 --> 00:08:22,773
What was the plan behind this whole mess?

66
00:08:23,565 --> 00:08:24,733
Did Chairman Hwang Hwa-san order this?

67
00:08:24,817 --> 00:08:27,653
I'm telling you,
I really don't know who they are!

68
00:08:28,112 --> 00:08:29,113
In-gu.

69
00:08:29,196 --> 00:08:30,823
Can't you see for yourself?

70
00:08:31,198 --> 00:08:34,076
- Beom-ryong's completely lost his edge.
- Ma Gong-bok!

71
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:36,120
He left that life behind and put
everything into the convenience store.

72
00:08:36,328 --> 00:08:39,123
He hasn't picked a single fight,
not even with the neighborhood punks.

73
00:08:39,248 --> 00:08:41,333
How could Kang Beom-ryong,
a convenience store owner

74
00:08:41,959 --> 00:08:45,796
possibly stand up
to a big boss like you, Yoo In-gu?

75
00:08:46,672 --> 00:08:48,090
For old times' sake...

76
00:08:48,298 --> 00:08:50,050
please let this go just this once.

77
00:08:50,342 --> 00:08:52,344
Damn, look at this shameless bastard.

78
00:08:54,054 --> 00:08:56,098
I'd like to grind you into dust

79
00:08:56,181 --> 00:08:57,182
and you're asking for old times' sake?

80
00:08:57,266 --> 00:08:58,475
I'm not letting you off easy.

81
00:08:58,559 --> 00:09:00,269
No, don't!

82
00:09:00,394 --> 00:09:01,687
Yoo In-gu, don't!

83
00:09:02,646 --> 00:09:05,941
You only need one arm
to scan barcodes at a convenience store.

84
00:09:06,024 --> 00:09:07,609
- No, don't!
- Grab him.

85
00:09:07,693 --> 00:09:08,819
No! I need both arms!

86
00:09:08,902 --> 00:09:10,362
I need both hands!

87
00:09:10,696 --> 00:09:12,614
In-gu! I mean...

88
00:09:12,990 --> 00:09:14,533
Boss. Sir!

89
00:09:14,658 --> 00:09:15,909
This was all my fault.

90
00:09:15,993 --> 00:09:17,452
I didn't know my place.

91
00:09:17,911 --> 00:09:19,371
I overstepped my bounds.

92
00:09:19,454 --> 00:09:21,498
It's all my fault. I apologize.

93
00:09:21,748 --> 00:09:22,749
So please...

94
00:09:23,208 --> 00:09:25,335
just give us one more chance. If you do...

95
00:09:26,503 --> 00:09:28,213
we'll do anything you say.

96
00:09:29,548 --> 00:09:30,549
Anything?

97
00:09:36,263 --> 00:09:37,556
Then bark like a dog.

98
00:09:44,521 --> 00:09:45,814
- Woof, woof!
- Boss!

99
00:09:45,898 --> 00:09:47,024
Woof, woof!

100
00:09:47,107 --> 00:09:49,151
Woof, woof!

101
00:09:51,195 --> 00:09:52,779
I'll bark instead!

102
00:09:53,322 --> 00:09:54,781
Woof, woof, woof, woof!

103
00:09:54,865 --> 00:09:57,492
Woof, woof, woof, woof, woof!

104
00:09:57,576 --> 00:09:59,077
Woof, woof, woof, woof!

105
00:09:59,161 --> 00:10:02,247
Woof, woof, woof, woof, woof!

106
00:10:02,331 --> 00:10:03,332
Woof!

107
00:10:05,417 --> 00:10:06,460
Stop it!

108
00:10:07,586 --> 00:10:09,713
Woof, woof, woof!

109
00:10:10,964 --> 00:10:15,385
Woof, woof, woof! Woof, woof, woof!

110
00:10:15,469 --> 00:10:16,970
Woof, woof, woof!

111
00:10:23,644 --> 00:10:24,853
Shut up!

112
00:10:31,276 --> 00:10:33,570
This is so touching,
it's making me tear up.

113
00:10:34,196 --> 00:10:36,448
Get them. Finish them off
before I change my mind.

114
00:10:36,823 --> 00:10:38,200
- We barked!
- No!

115
00:10:38,283 --> 00:10:39,785
I barked!

116
00:10:39,868 --> 00:10:41,536
We barked!

117
00:10:42,496 --> 00:10:43,497
You bastard.

118
00:10:43,789 --> 00:10:44,790
Hold on.

119
00:10:45,874 --> 00:10:47,459
Sergeant Kim, what is it?
I'm busy right now.

120
00:10:47,542 --> 00:10:49,628
Sir, are you at Yeongseon Food
by any chance?

121
00:10:49,795 --> 00:10:52,756
An anonymous assault report
was just filed at Yeongseon Food.

122
00:10:52,839 --> 00:10:54,841
If a unit is dispatched now,
they'll be there in ten minutes.

123
00:10:55,008 --> 00:10:56,843
A report? Which bastard did it?

124
00:10:57,052 --> 00:10:59,096
Please, just call it a day and wrap it up.

125
00:10:59,179 --> 00:11:00,889
Hey, can't you even cover up
something like this?

126
00:11:01,098 --> 00:11:02,641
You should at least be worth
what I pay you, damn it.

127
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:06,603
The report has already been filed.
There's nothing I can do.

128
00:11:06,853 --> 00:11:08,188
For now, just get out of there.

129
00:11:08,272 --> 00:11:09,940
I'll delay the dispatch as long as I can.

130
00:11:21,201 --> 00:11:22,452
Hey, Kang Beom-ryong.

131
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:26,164
If you're just a country mutt,
wear a leash and guard a house.

132
00:11:26,665 --> 00:11:29,626
Stop wandering around causing trouble,
unless you want to get yourself killed.

133
00:11:38,385 --> 00:11:39,386
But.

134
00:11:40,429 --> 00:11:42,806
It's been too long
to say goodbye like this, right?

135
00:11:49,438 --> 00:11:51,315
Boss, are you okay?

136
00:11:56,028 --> 00:11:57,029
YEONGSEON FOOD

137
00:11:57,112 --> 00:11:59,406
THE PRIDE OF KOREA PORK PREMIUM JERKY
YEONGSEON FOOD

138
00:12:07,998 --> 00:12:08,999
- Oh, my back.
- Boss, are you okay?

139
00:12:09,124 --> 00:12:11,335
Gosh, get this off me.

140
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:20,761
Why won't this come off?

141
00:12:21,094 --> 00:12:22,095
Are you okay?

142
00:12:35,025 --> 00:12:36,735
I'm giving you exactly three days.

143
00:12:36,818 --> 00:12:38,111
If you're not out by then

144
00:12:38,195 --> 00:12:39,654
we're forcibly demolishing this place.

145
00:12:39,738 --> 00:12:41,573
Forced demolition, sir?

146
00:12:42,407 --> 00:12:44,785
And if you want to report this,
go right ahead.

147
00:12:45,243 --> 00:12:47,788
But who do you think is faster?
The cops or us?

148
00:12:48,330 --> 00:12:49,790
If you're curious, give it a try.

149
00:12:49,873 --> 00:12:51,083
You get what I'm saying, high schooler?

150
00:12:52,125 --> 00:12:53,919
- Nam-il...
- Let's go.

151
00:12:54,836 --> 00:12:56,380
Nam-il.

152
00:12:56,755 --> 00:13:00,175
Nam-il, Nam-il.

153
00:13:00,258 --> 00:13:02,177
Are you okay? Nam-il.

154
00:13:02,803 --> 00:13:05,389
- Nam-il, are you okay?
- Uncle...

155
00:13:06,098 --> 00:13:07,349
They're gone.

156
00:13:07,432 --> 00:13:08,433
Uncle...

157
00:13:09,059 --> 00:13:10,227
They're gone...

158
00:13:15,774 --> 00:13:16,775
Boss.

159
00:13:16,858 --> 00:13:18,443
If you're really worried...

160
00:13:18,860 --> 00:13:20,487
should I get some skilled guys

161
00:13:20,821 --> 00:13:22,322
to put the screws on him?

162
00:13:22,989 --> 00:13:24,282
Skilled guys?

163
00:13:24,366 --> 00:13:26,243
That Kang Beom-ryong guy

164
00:13:26,326 --> 00:13:27,953
he seems to have lost his bite

165
00:13:28,036 --> 00:13:29,246
so why don't we wait for the right moment

166
00:13:29,329 --> 00:13:30,831
and take care of him quietly?

167
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:34,334
ONE UNREAD MESSAGE

168
00:13:34,418 --> 00:13:36,586
KIM BANG-GON
I JUST ARRIVED AT CHAIRMAN DO'S CASINO

169
00:13:38,380 --> 00:13:39,381
Forget it.

170
00:13:39,464 --> 00:13:40,841
We need to lay low for a while.

171
00:13:41,842 --> 00:13:43,468
He's at Chairman Do's casino right now.

172
00:13:43,552 --> 00:13:44,553
Chairman Do?

173
00:13:44,803 --> 00:13:45,887
Isn't he on a business trip in the States?

174
00:13:45,971 --> 00:13:48,807
I don't know. What is that sly fox
plotting by coming back like this?

175
00:13:49,933 --> 00:13:51,893
We need to keep an eye
on Chairman Do for a while.

176
00:13:51,977 --> 00:13:53,937
- You know what I mean?
- Understood, Boss.

177
00:13:54,396 --> 00:13:56,064
Anyway, that bastard Kang Beom-ryong...

178
00:13:56,148 --> 00:13:58,024
he's got some damn good luck.

179
00:14:22,382 --> 00:14:24,092
I told you, if you're tired,
get some rest.

180
00:14:24,718 --> 00:14:25,719
No, I'm fine.

181
00:14:26,511 --> 00:14:27,637
You must be tired too.

182
00:14:28,430 --> 00:14:29,514
Tired? Please.

183
00:14:29,598 --> 00:14:32,642
You think a few weak punches
like that would faze me?

184
00:14:33,018 --> 00:14:35,312
I just didn't get any sleep last night

185
00:14:35,395 --> 00:14:36,771
so I was a little off my game.

186
00:14:37,647 --> 00:14:38,899
If I hadn't frozen up

187
00:14:38,982 --> 00:14:41,401
I would've wiped the floor
with those bastards, damn it.

188
00:14:46,156 --> 00:14:47,199
I'm sorry.

189
00:14:48,867 --> 00:14:50,243
What's with the sudden apology?
That's not like you.

190
00:14:50,327 --> 00:14:52,162
Because I went after Jeong Ho-myeong...

191
00:14:53,038 --> 00:14:55,499
I ended up dragging Yoo In-gu into this.

192
00:14:55,999 --> 00:14:58,043
From now on, I'm going to
stop chasing Jeong Ho-myeong

193
00:14:58,460 --> 00:14:59,669
and getting revenge for the Chairman...

194
00:15:00,504 --> 00:15:02,672
I'm giving it all up.

195
00:15:04,090 --> 00:15:05,091
What?

196
00:15:06,009 --> 00:15:08,053
- What? Why?
- The one who ruined Heaven Capital

197
00:15:08,261 --> 00:15:09,679
wasn't Jeong Ho-myeong.

198
00:15:11,014 --> 00:15:12,140
God, seriously.

199
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:14,100
I was such an idiot to get it wrong.

200
00:15:14,351 --> 00:15:16,186
And now Yoo In-gu is on our tail.

201
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:18,146
No, but really...

202
00:15:18,230 --> 00:15:19,356
I think just forgetting

203
00:15:19,648 --> 00:15:21,399
about the past and moving on

204
00:15:21,942 --> 00:15:22,984
is the only way.

205
00:15:23,985 --> 00:15:25,570
You're really just going to forget it all?

206
00:15:25,654 --> 00:15:26,655
Yes.

207
00:15:26,905 --> 00:15:29,241
Like you said, from now on I'll just...

208
00:15:30,033 --> 00:15:31,076
live a normal life.

209
00:15:31,660 --> 00:15:32,869
Just working at the convenience store.

210
00:15:33,954 --> 00:15:35,539
I'll try my best to live that way.

211
00:15:43,338 --> 00:15:44,506
Good grief.

212
00:15:45,799 --> 00:15:48,218
Well, have a good one.

213
00:15:50,595 --> 00:15:52,264
Don't go. Hey, where are you going?

214
00:15:53,974 --> 00:15:54,975
Gong-bok.

215
00:15:58,770 --> 00:15:59,813
What...

216
00:16:00,230 --> 00:16:01,898
- Was the convenience store robbed?
- Sorry?

217
00:16:02,899 --> 00:16:04,568
No, I mean...

218
00:16:04,651 --> 00:16:06,152
- your face!
- No.

219
00:16:06,820 --> 00:16:09,239
Oh, no. This? It's nothing.

220
00:16:14,953 --> 00:16:16,329
Was it gangsters?

221
00:16:19,082 --> 00:16:20,959
Gangsters?

222
00:16:21,585 --> 00:16:22,586
No, that's not it.

223
00:16:22,669 --> 00:16:24,796
I've been seeing a lot of gangsters around
the casino lately.

224
00:16:25,630 --> 00:16:27,382
You're having trouble with them,
aren't you?

225
00:16:27,465 --> 00:16:30,885
- Those bastards!
- No! No, it's not like that.

226
00:16:31,136 --> 00:16:32,304
I'm sorry.

227
00:16:32,387 --> 00:16:33,638
It wasn't gangsters.

228
00:16:33,722 --> 00:16:36,141
It was just some drunk customers
making a scene.

229
00:16:36,224 --> 00:16:37,934
But I talked them down

230
00:16:38,018 --> 00:16:39,269
so you really don't need to report it.

231
00:16:42,230 --> 00:16:44,190
- But still...
- Oh, right!

232
00:16:44,274 --> 00:16:46,192
You're here for a lunch box, aren't you?

233
00:16:46,401 --> 00:16:47,694
I wonder if any of these are okay.

234
00:17:06,796 --> 00:17:09,549
That wound could get infected
if you're not careful.

235
00:17:20,018 --> 00:17:21,269
Even if you don't report it

236
00:17:21,353 --> 00:17:22,812
you should at least treat it.

237
00:17:25,815 --> 00:17:26,816
Treat it...

238
00:17:28,735 --> 00:17:29,903
Anyway...

239
00:17:29,986 --> 00:17:31,780
whether it's drunks or gangsters

240
00:17:31,863 --> 00:17:33,615
people who just throw their weight around

241
00:17:33,698 --> 00:17:36,701
and hurt people should be
taken off the streets.

242
00:17:36,785 --> 00:17:38,995
So if this happens again

243
00:17:39,079 --> 00:17:40,705
you have to report it.

244
00:17:41,373 --> 00:17:42,374
Okay.

245
00:17:42,457 --> 00:17:43,458
And...

246
00:17:43,958 --> 00:17:46,127
if you feel uncomfortable reporting...

247
00:17:48,004 --> 00:17:49,422
you can call me directly.

248
00:17:50,757 --> 00:17:52,050
JUSTICE IS ALIVE
OFFICER PARK MI-KYUNG

249
00:17:52,133 --> 00:17:54,761
I didn't know police officers carried
business cards like these.

250
00:17:54,844 --> 00:17:56,137
I had them made myself.

251
00:17:56,429 --> 00:17:57,639
It's a limited edition of 100.

252
00:17:57,722 --> 00:17:59,849
Wow, a limited edition. This is valuable.

253
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:00,934
Why give one to me?

254
00:18:01,017 --> 00:18:03,228
Hard-working citizens like you

255
00:18:04,104 --> 00:18:05,980
are who police officers
like me are here to protect.

256
00:18:06,064 --> 00:18:07,399
So please...

257
00:18:07,691 --> 00:18:08,817
be sure to call.

258
00:18:09,484 --> 00:18:10,944
Call me.

259
00:18:11,486 --> 00:18:13,822
- Okay.
- Okay.

260
00:18:17,784 --> 00:18:18,785
Take care.

261
00:18:28,128 --> 00:18:29,170
I'm sorry, Boss.

262
00:18:30,130 --> 00:18:31,548
Go and find happiness

263
00:18:32,132 --> 00:18:33,717
in an ordinary life.

264
00:18:34,926 --> 00:18:36,010
What I started...

265
00:18:36,886 --> 00:18:38,972
I'll finish myself.

266
00:18:40,890 --> 00:18:42,350
What? Are you sure?

267
00:18:42,434 --> 00:18:43,727
It was Bulgae?

268
00:18:44,185 --> 00:18:45,311
I'm sure.

269
00:18:45,937 --> 00:18:47,605
The dress he wore

270
00:18:47,689 --> 00:18:49,357
on the ferry ten years ago

271
00:18:49,441 --> 00:18:50,483
was in his house.

272
00:18:50,650 --> 00:18:52,485
What about the item? Did you find it too?

273
00:18:52,944 --> 00:18:54,738
I searched everywhere

274
00:18:55,989 --> 00:18:57,407
but the receiver wasn't responding.

275
00:18:58,950 --> 00:19:00,285
I don't think it's in the house.

276
00:19:01,369 --> 00:19:03,872
I think we need to take a different

277
00:19:04,414 --> 00:19:06,249
more careful approach.

278
00:19:06,332 --> 00:19:07,667
Why?

279
00:19:07,751 --> 00:19:08,793
Is something wrong?

280
00:19:09,252 --> 00:19:10,587
Do you think Bulgae is just some nobody?

281
00:19:11,421 --> 00:19:13,173
He stayed on Yeongseon Island
for ten years

282
00:19:13,256 --> 00:19:14,758
and even got a job.

283
00:19:15,675 --> 00:19:17,844
And he infiltrated that family
with the grandchild.

284
00:19:18,303 --> 00:19:19,554
It could be a trap.

285
00:19:20,096 --> 00:19:21,097
A trap?

286
00:19:21,181 --> 00:19:22,390
At Yeongseon Food...

287
00:19:23,016 --> 00:19:24,976
Bulgae wasn't the only one there.

288
00:19:26,519 --> 00:19:27,896
The guy with the forehead scar

289
00:19:27,979 --> 00:19:30,023
the high school kid, the hick.

290
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:31,608
And...

291
00:19:32,150 --> 00:19:34,402
the regular, Oldboy.

292
00:19:35,069 --> 00:19:37,989
Him being with Bulgae just doesn't add up.

293
00:19:38,490 --> 00:19:39,741
It could be a coincidence.

294
00:19:40,074 --> 00:19:41,701
The guy's been lurking around me
for ten years

295
00:19:41,785 --> 00:19:44,454
and he just happens to be getting
beaten up with Bulgae?

296
00:19:44,537 --> 00:19:45,538
You know it too.

297
00:19:45,622 --> 00:19:46,623
At that time...

298
00:19:46,873 --> 00:19:48,208
there was a third person.

299
00:19:49,584 --> 00:19:51,628
Let's start by digging into
what's right in front of us

300
00:19:51,711 --> 00:19:53,463
one step at a time.

301
00:19:54,255 --> 00:19:55,673
This Oldboy guy...

302
00:19:56,382 --> 00:19:57,759
I'll go have a talk with him.

303
00:19:58,468 --> 00:19:59,552
Ho-myeong.

304
00:19:59,803 --> 00:20:01,805
We're so close. Be careful.

305
00:20:02,013 --> 00:20:03,097
This is your first mission in ten years.

306
00:20:03,181 --> 00:20:04,808
Oh, come on!

307
00:20:05,809 --> 00:20:06,935
Have you forgotten who I am?

308
00:20:32,168 --> 00:20:34,838
SEPTEMBER 2010

309
00:22:08,264 --> 00:22:10,767
Going with the classic method, are we?

310
00:22:24,197 --> 00:22:26,157
MANAGER LEE

311
00:22:29,911 --> 00:22:31,454
- Hello?
- Manager Bong.

312
00:22:31,955 --> 00:22:34,415
You can't just not show up
for work without calling.

313
00:22:34,499 --> 00:22:35,750
Manager Lee.

314
00:22:36,542 --> 00:22:39,087
I'm feeling really sick.

315
00:22:41,381 --> 00:22:44,300
Look, I can't cover for you anymore.

316
00:22:44,384 --> 00:22:46,594
I'll be there tomorrow
even if I have to crawl in.

317
00:22:46,678 --> 00:22:47,804
Just this one time...

318
00:22:47,887 --> 00:22:49,263
If you continue to have

319
00:22:49,555 --> 00:22:51,766
unexcused absences,
you will be terminated.

320
00:22:52,016 --> 00:22:54,227
I... I really...

321
00:23:04,487 --> 00:23:05,488
Damn it.

322
00:23:53,578 --> 00:23:55,621
JUSTICE IS ALIVE
OFFICER PARK MI-KYUNG

323
00:23:57,957 --> 00:24:00,585
JUSTICE IS ALIVE
OFFICER PARK MI-KYUNG

324
00:24:18,436 --> 00:24:22,148
JUMBO24
FRIENDLY CONVENIENCE STORE

325
00:24:22,231 --> 00:24:28,988
YEONGSEON POLICE SUBSTATION

326
00:24:52,678 --> 00:24:53,679
Sir.

327
00:24:53,763 --> 00:24:54,931
What are you doing, kid?

328
00:24:56,557 --> 00:24:57,767
Are you going to a wedding?

329
00:25:00,561 --> 00:25:01,562
Yes.

330
00:25:02,647 --> 00:25:03,815
I'm going far away.

331
00:25:06,109 --> 00:25:07,110
Listen, sir.

332
00:25:08,694 --> 00:25:09,695
I...

333
00:25:11,823 --> 00:25:13,616
made sure to stock up on Seoraksan.

334
00:25:14,408 --> 00:25:15,660
So I hope you'll continue

335
00:25:15,743 --> 00:25:17,036
to shop here...

336
00:25:18,329 --> 00:25:19,330
here at our store.

337
00:25:20,331 --> 00:25:21,332
Please.

338
00:25:22,416 --> 00:25:23,417
What's gotten into you?

339
00:25:53,156 --> 00:25:54,240
Surprise!

340
00:25:54,490 --> 00:25:56,409
- You're early, President Yoo.
- Early?

341
00:25:56,492 --> 00:25:58,119
You drag me out here at the crack of dawn

342
00:25:58,202 --> 00:25:59,537
and you're just stuffing your face?

343
00:25:59,620 --> 00:26:00,913
You're still a real piece of work.

344
00:26:00,997 --> 00:26:02,415
A leopard can't change its spots.

345
00:26:02,498 --> 00:26:03,958
Want some brunch?

346
00:26:04,250 --> 00:26:07,253
CHAIRMAN OF HEAVEN HOTEL AND CASINO
DO HYEON-TAE

347
00:26:07,336 --> 00:26:08,671
Are you trying to give me an ulcer?

348
00:26:09,046 --> 00:26:10,214
Just get to the point.

349
00:26:11,674 --> 00:26:12,675
Okay.

350
00:26:14,635 --> 00:26:15,636
All right.

351
00:26:15,720 --> 00:26:17,513
I'll get right to business. Have a seat.

352
00:26:17,805 --> 00:26:18,806
Hey, Director.

353
00:26:20,433 --> 00:26:21,434
All right.

354
00:26:27,899 --> 00:26:30,151
I heard you beat up my security staff
a few days ago.

355
00:26:30,818 --> 00:26:32,904
I mean, how can you
treat salaried employees

356
00:26:32,987 --> 00:26:35,031
like they're some street punks?

357
00:26:35,239 --> 00:26:36,616
A man in your position should know better.

358
00:26:36,699 --> 00:26:39,327
Damn it. I was trying
to be nice about this.

359
00:26:40,953 --> 00:26:42,371
So what? You want me to
pay their medical bills?

360
00:26:42,455 --> 00:26:44,123
No! No.

361
00:26:44,707 --> 00:26:47,168
I can take care of their medical bills.

362
00:26:48,544 --> 00:26:50,838
But something just occurred to me.

363
00:26:51,923 --> 00:26:52,924
Why?

364
00:26:53,549 --> 00:26:55,092
I don't understand. Why?

365
00:26:56,177 --> 00:26:58,638
Don't give me that English crap
and speak Korean.

366
00:26:58,721 --> 00:27:01,432
Why would you go so far
as to beat up my security staff

367
00:27:01,515 --> 00:27:03,392
just to check the CCTV footage?

368
00:27:03,851 --> 00:27:05,519
What exactly was on that footage?

369
00:27:07,271 --> 00:27:09,774
Is there some kind of problem

370
00:27:09,857 --> 00:27:11,651
at Heaven Capital?
That's what I'm wondering.

371
00:27:12,610 --> 00:27:13,819
Stop trying to test me.

372
00:27:13,903 --> 00:27:14,904
Test you?

373
00:27:15,238 --> 00:27:17,782
Come on, why would I test you?
I don't have time for that.

374
00:27:18,741 --> 00:27:21,494
President Yoo, any problem
with your business?

375
00:27:22,036 --> 00:27:24,038
- Stupid.
- You wannabe Yankee bastard.

376
00:27:24,121 --> 00:27:25,706
I told you to speak Korean! Damn it.

377
00:27:32,505 --> 00:27:34,215
This bastard... Damn it.

378
00:27:35,883 --> 00:27:36,884
This guy...

379
00:27:41,931 --> 00:27:43,683
Whoa, calm down.

380
00:27:43,766 --> 00:27:45,184
Calm down, man. Director Nam.

381
00:27:47,311 --> 00:27:49,313
Jeez, why is everyone so worked up?

382
00:27:49,522 --> 00:27:50,564
Huh? It's so vulgar.

383
00:27:51,148 --> 00:27:53,693
I was just asking out of
concern for you, President Yoo.

384
00:27:53,818 --> 00:27:55,236
- Concern?
- Yeah.

385
00:27:55,820 --> 00:27:56,821
President Yoo.

386
00:27:57,071 --> 00:27:59,490
Heaven Capital, your business, but...

387
00:27:59,657 --> 00:28:02,243
Heaven Hotel and Casino,
my business. So...

388
00:28:02,952 --> 00:28:04,704
We're in the same boat here,
called Heaven.

389
00:28:04,787 --> 00:28:06,080
If you cause trouble

390
00:28:06,163 --> 00:28:07,331
and word gets back to Chief Han

391
00:28:07,415 --> 00:28:09,542
it'll be a problem for both of us, okay?

392
00:28:09,959 --> 00:28:12,336
We're co-workers in the same boat. Right?

393
00:28:12,670 --> 00:28:14,422
When trouble comes,
we gotta help each other, right?

394
00:28:14,505 --> 00:28:16,632
Help me? You?

395
00:28:17,216 --> 00:28:18,634
What a load of bullshit.

396
00:28:18,968 --> 00:28:20,970
You'd be the first one to
take over my business if I go down.

397
00:28:23,973 --> 00:28:25,599
I'll handle this myself

398
00:28:25,850 --> 00:28:27,768
so just shut your mouth. Got it?

399
00:28:28,227 --> 00:28:29,854
Oh, "shut my mouth."

400
00:28:30,730 --> 00:28:31,731
Okay.

401
00:28:31,939 --> 00:28:32,940
No problem.

402
00:28:33,566 --> 00:28:34,567
Bye.

403
00:28:35,359 --> 00:28:36,444
He won't even accept my help.

404
00:28:41,032 --> 00:28:42,033
Well.

405
00:28:45,036 --> 00:28:47,246
President Yoo's drug-laced beef jerky
is going around the casino.

406
00:28:47,580 --> 00:28:48,581
Drugs?

407
00:28:53,544 --> 00:28:54,920
Damn.

408
00:28:55,212 --> 00:28:56,422
President Yoo has been busy.

409
00:28:56,630 --> 00:28:58,549
I think getting involved
could be a problem.

410
00:28:59,258 --> 00:29:00,468
Should I report this to Chief Han?

411
00:29:07,558 --> 00:29:08,684
For now...

412
00:29:09,143 --> 00:29:10,853
let's just keep this to ourselves.

413
00:29:13,230 --> 00:29:14,231
Instead...

414
00:29:15,191 --> 00:29:16,359
why don't we

415
00:29:16,442 --> 00:29:19,403
take a closer look at this jerky business?

416
00:29:19,862 --> 00:29:21,489
If the business model is solid

417
00:29:21,572 --> 00:29:23,449
it wouldn't be a bad idea
for us to take it over.

418
00:29:23,949 --> 00:29:26,202
And keep a close eye
on the Heaven Capital situation.

419
00:29:26,285 --> 00:29:28,704
Yes, I'll look into it and report back.

420
00:29:41,509 --> 00:29:43,427
I told you to make sure the security team
kept their mouths shut.

421
00:29:43,636 --> 00:29:44,970
Can't you do one thing right?

422
00:29:45,471 --> 00:29:47,848
You might as well advertise
that we have a problem.

423
00:29:48,140 --> 00:29:49,183
I'm sorry, sir.

424
00:29:50,017 --> 00:29:51,102
You little...

425
00:29:58,067 --> 00:29:59,777
Stop following me
and get the car. Damn it.

426
00:30:03,906 --> 00:30:06,283
The number you have dialed is unavailable.
Please leave a message...

427
00:30:40,651 --> 00:30:42,236
I've had enough.

428
00:30:42,987 --> 00:30:45,614
- That's enough.
- Take more!

429
00:31:17,605 --> 00:31:19,732
Are you from a newspaper?

430
00:31:20,441 --> 00:31:21,984
Or a TV station?

431
00:31:22,193 --> 00:31:23,235
Hello.

432
00:31:23,319 --> 00:31:25,863
I'm sorry. I should have
introduced myself sooner.

433
00:31:26,322 --> 00:31:28,282
I'm from the Criminal Division of the
Imcheon District Prosecutors' Office

434
00:31:29,033 --> 00:31:30,367
Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae.

435
00:31:32,661 --> 00:31:34,622
I'd like to ask you a few questions.

436
00:31:34,705 --> 00:31:36,123
What would a prosecutor want

437
00:31:36,207 --> 00:31:38,167
with a washed-up old man like me?

438
00:31:38,792 --> 00:31:41,170
I've just been cooped up in my room

439
00:31:41,253 --> 00:31:44,131
so I don't know much
about the outside world.

440
00:31:44,215 --> 00:31:45,424
Ten years ago.

441
00:31:45,758 --> 00:31:47,843
the murder of the
National Security Advisor, Kwon Soon-bok.

442
00:31:48,302 --> 00:31:50,971
It's the case that put you in prison

443
00:31:51,055 --> 00:31:52,223
so you should know more
about it than anyone.

444
00:31:52,306 --> 00:31:54,475
That case is closed.

445
00:31:56,060 --> 00:31:57,686
So why are you asking about it?

446
00:31:57,770 --> 00:31:59,772
If the real culprit was never caught...

447
00:32:00,564 --> 00:32:02,107
then the case isn't closed, is it?

448
00:32:02,942 --> 00:32:05,861
And I'm not talking about it
being a personal grudge.

449
00:32:06,153 --> 00:32:08,280
Or that it was ordered by one of
Kwon Soon-bok's political rivals.

450
00:32:08,364 --> 00:32:10,241
Forget those tabloid rumors.

451
00:32:11,283 --> 00:32:13,285
Please tell me the truth.

452
00:32:14,245 --> 00:32:15,871
The person who framed you for murder

453
00:32:15,955 --> 00:32:18,916
and put you in prison...

454
00:32:21,919 --> 00:32:23,254
was this person, wasn't it?

455
00:32:31,762 --> 00:32:34,265
I don't know what you're talking about.

456
00:32:34,807 --> 00:32:35,808
Jeez...

457
00:32:36,183 --> 00:32:39,603
- Mr. Hwang Hwa-san.
- If you're going to use tabloid stories

458
00:32:40,062 --> 00:32:41,814
at least pick a believable one.

459
00:32:43,315 --> 00:32:44,316
Good grief.

460
00:32:44,567 --> 00:32:46,360
Are you really that scared
of Han Gyeong-wook?

461
00:32:55,536 --> 00:32:56,787
Prosecutor.

462
00:32:57,121 --> 00:32:59,748
I lost the organization
I spent my entire life building

463
00:32:59,832 --> 00:33:02,751
and now I'm rotting
in a cell in my old age.

464
00:33:02,835 --> 00:33:04,503
At this point...

465
00:33:04,962 --> 00:33:07,089
what could I possibly
have to be afraid of?

466
00:33:08,424 --> 00:33:11,844
I'm just tired of being used
and getting nothing in return.

467
00:33:11,927 --> 00:33:15,306
That's what I can't stand.

468
00:33:17,141 --> 00:33:18,684
I'm not trying to use you.

469
00:33:19,268 --> 00:33:21,353
I'm proposing a win-win situation.

470
00:33:21,604 --> 00:33:22,938
I need to solve this case.

471
00:33:23,022 --> 00:33:25,232
And you need a chance to get out of here.

472
00:33:28,652 --> 00:33:30,321
For it to be a win-win...

473
00:33:30,946 --> 00:33:35,492
shouldn't I get out of prison first?

474
00:33:36,827 --> 00:33:40,039
Bring me the person who really killed
Chief Kwon Soon-bok.

475
00:33:41,332 --> 00:33:44,209
Then we'll talk.

476
00:33:48,922 --> 00:33:50,299
So you do know who the real killer is.

477
00:33:53,594 --> 00:33:55,012
Who is it?

478
00:34:00,684 --> 00:34:02,603
It wasn't...

479
00:34:03,062 --> 00:34:05,064
a person.

480
00:34:05,981 --> 00:34:08,192
It was a mutt...

481
00:34:09,735 --> 00:34:11,654
that I raised.

482
00:34:20,287 --> 00:34:23,082
Damn, she's scurrying all over the place.

483
00:34:23,290 --> 00:34:24,625
She's not Nongae, she's a stray dog.

484
00:34:25,501 --> 00:34:27,002
Should I report in now?

485
00:34:27,544 --> 00:34:28,712
Hold on.

486
00:34:28,962 --> 00:34:30,631
Let's see where she's headed first.

487
00:34:42,393 --> 00:34:44,687
RESTRICTED NUMBER

488
00:34:50,901 --> 00:34:52,194
This is Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae.

489
00:34:52,277 --> 00:34:53,362
Prosecutor Gang.

490
00:34:53,445 --> 00:34:55,781
Poking your nose around
isn't going to solve anything.

491
00:34:56,240 --> 00:34:58,992
You should be watching your back.

492
00:34:59,451 --> 00:35:01,662
- Who is this?
- I can't tell you that yet.

493
00:35:02,162 --> 00:35:03,747
The people in the white car
ahead of you...

494
00:35:04,456 --> 00:35:05,457
don't they look familiar?

495
00:35:12,047 --> 00:35:13,048
You see the road ahead?

496
00:35:13,465 --> 00:35:15,092
Go straight through the intersection.

497
00:35:15,384 --> 00:35:16,885
I'll take care of the rest.

498
00:35:16,969 --> 00:35:18,178
Wait. Hello?

499
00:35:32,609 --> 00:35:35,112
ESTABLISHING LAW AND ORDER

500
00:35:58,552 --> 00:36:00,220
- Hey, what the...
- Ma'am.

501
00:36:00,304 --> 00:36:01,597
- What's going on?
- Are you okay?

502
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:03,265
We're the police.

503
00:36:03,724 --> 00:36:04,933
- Excuse me.
- Ma'am.

504
00:36:05,058 --> 00:36:06,852
Ma'am, are you okay? Ma'am?

505
00:36:07,060 --> 00:36:08,395
- Excuse me.
- Hello, ma'am?

506
00:36:08,479 --> 00:36:09,730
- Hello?
- What should we do?

507
00:36:12,441 --> 00:36:13,525
What?

508
00:36:13,609 --> 00:36:14,610
What is happening?

509
00:36:14,985 --> 00:36:16,695
What's with her?

510
00:36:17,321 --> 00:36:18,322
Mister.

511
00:36:18,530 --> 00:36:19,531
What the...

512
00:36:38,842 --> 00:36:39,843
Nice to meet you.

513
00:36:40,594 --> 00:36:41,595
Hello.

514
00:36:42,513 --> 00:36:43,764
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
- Hello.

515
00:36:45,224 --> 00:36:46,225
Thank you for coming all this way.

516
00:36:46,308 --> 00:36:47,726
I'll escort you inside.

517
00:36:58,487 --> 00:37:00,864
Why does it have to be so
meticulous and long-winded...

518
00:37:01,448 --> 00:37:05,619
VICE PRESIDENT, TOYO FINANCE, TOKYO
RYUSEIGUMI CLAN YAKUZA, NAKATOMO RYUICHI

519
00:37:09,456 --> 00:37:11,500
HEAD OF FUTURE STRATEGY, HUNAN
CONSTRUCTION, CHINESE TRIAD EXECUTIVE

520
00:37:11,583 --> 00:37:13,252
LI GUOFENG

521
00:37:13,544 --> 00:37:15,546
The project hasn't even started.

522
00:37:16,296 --> 00:37:18,090
That's what it says, right?

523
00:37:18,298 --> 00:37:21,885
Land acquisition usually involves
a lot of procedures

524
00:37:22,010 --> 00:37:23,095
and it’s already been several months.

525
00:37:23,262 --> 00:37:24,346
But I heard that

526
00:37:24,429 --> 00:37:26,640
the city government
is still delaying the approval.

527
00:37:27,182 --> 00:37:30,519
I’m starting to question whether
you’re actually capable of handling this.

528
00:37:34,898 --> 00:37:37,901
It's true that
the project has been delayed

529
00:37:38,193 --> 00:37:39,987
but this was something
we fully anticipated.

530
00:37:40,487 --> 00:37:42,906
Once I win the mayoral election

531
00:37:42,990 --> 00:37:45,450
the permit issues
will be resolved immediately.

532
00:37:45,701 --> 00:37:49,329
After that, the project will begin
to gain momentum

533
00:37:49,705 --> 00:37:50,956
so I ask for your patience

534
00:37:51,707 --> 00:37:52,708
and to just wait and see.

535
00:37:54,918 --> 00:37:56,128
Of course.

536
00:37:57,045 --> 00:38:03,010
The difference in approval ratings
between them is only 0.5%.

537
00:38:03,427 --> 00:38:06,805
Can you really say
with certainty that he will win?

538
00:38:06,972 --> 00:38:12,394
And I've heard that the opposing candidate
has strong connections to Imcheon.

539
00:38:13,896 --> 00:38:16,440
Isn't it entirely possible
for things to be overturned?

540
00:38:33,248 --> 00:38:34,333
What about Kim Seon-jung?

541
00:38:35,459 --> 00:38:36,919
He's proving to be
more difficult than we expected.

542
00:38:37,169 --> 00:38:38,545
No matter how much
we dig through his accounts

543
00:38:38,629 --> 00:38:40,213
we can't find any dirt on him.

544
00:38:40,923 --> 00:38:42,466
REPORT ON CANDIDATE KIM SEON-JUNG

545
00:38:42,549 --> 00:38:44,384
And there's nothing
we can turn into a scandal?

546
00:38:44,468 --> 00:38:46,345
Ever since his days as a teacher
on Yeongseon Island

547
00:38:46,428 --> 00:38:48,263
he's been highly respected by everyone.

548
00:38:48,347 --> 00:38:50,182
We couldn't even find a single rumor
about him taking bribes.

549
00:38:50,682 --> 00:38:52,100
We looked into his relationships

550
00:38:52,184 --> 00:38:53,936
but his only family is his wife.

551
00:38:54,353 --> 00:38:57,147
His wife is the director of an
orphanage called Jaae Won

552
00:38:57,397 --> 00:38:58,649
and she also has an excellent reputation.

553
00:38:59,983 --> 00:39:02,569
So he's lived a squeaky-clean life?

554
00:39:04,071 --> 00:39:05,280
DEPOSIT AND WITHDRAWL RECORDS
OF KIM SEON-JUNG IN THE LAST YEAR

555
00:39:05,364 --> 00:39:06,949
Kim Seon-jung also acts as a sponsor

556
00:39:07,032 --> 00:39:10,577
and he seems to have a special interest
in the orphanage.

557
00:39:12,955 --> 00:39:14,331
Should we dig a little deeper
into that connection?

558
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:16,458
Just arrange a meeting.

559
00:39:18,210 --> 00:39:20,587
No matter how squeaky clean he is

560
00:39:20,921 --> 00:39:22,923
it only takes a few storms
to turn the water muddy...

561
00:39:23,340 --> 00:39:24,424
It happens in an instant.

562
00:39:25,550 --> 00:39:26,802
Set it up as soon as possible.

563
00:39:27,427 --> 00:39:28,428
Yes, sir.

564
00:39:50,951 --> 00:39:51,994
Oh, hello.

565
00:39:52,077 --> 00:39:54,705
You're Mr. Jeong
from Oran Chinese Restaurant, right?

566
00:39:54,788 --> 00:39:56,456
Wow, it's great to see you.

567
00:39:56,540 --> 00:39:59,001
But... why am I tied up like this?

568
00:39:59,334 --> 00:40:01,461
"You're Mr. Jeong
from Oran Chinese Restaurant, right?"

569
00:40:04,756 --> 00:40:08,802
I should've known when you kept ordering
those unpopular fried dumplings.

570
00:40:09,302 --> 00:40:10,303
What?

571
00:40:10,762 --> 00:40:12,514
Sir, what do you mean by that?

572
00:40:12,597 --> 00:40:14,683
Why have you been hanging
around me for ten years

573
00:40:14,766 --> 00:40:16,810
eating nothing but fried dumplings?

574
00:40:18,770 --> 00:40:19,896
What do you mean, why?

575
00:40:19,980 --> 00:40:21,565
I went because
the fried dumplings are delicious.

576
00:40:23,692 --> 00:40:24,735
- Is that so?
- Yes.

577
00:40:26,361 --> 00:40:28,363
Right. That's what I expected you to say.

578
00:40:30,032 --> 00:40:31,074
This here.

579
00:40:31,867 --> 00:40:34,369
It's been a while since I've used this.
I wonder if it'll still work.

580
00:40:36,204 --> 00:40:37,205
You know

581
00:40:37,289 --> 00:40:39,416
this is what the guys at the CIA use.

582
00:40:40,292 --> 00:40:41,877
It's a truth serum.

583
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:44,755
One shot of this,
and you'll spill everything you know.

584
00:40:46,214 --> 00:40:48,008
It was probably
because of all those criminals

585
00:40:48,091 --> 00:40:49,676
wasting time, pleading the fifth
or whatever

586
00:40:49,760 --> 00:40:51,720
that they got pissed off
and developed this in secret.

587
00:40:51,803 --> 00:40:53,638
The effect is amazing.

588
00:40:54,347 --> 00:40:56,641
There's just one unfortunate side effect.

589
00:40:59,311 --> 00:41:00,771
If you're unlucky

590
00:41:01,063 --> 00:41:02,814
there's about a 50%...

591
00:41:04,232 --> 00:41:05,233
chance.

592
00:41:09,446 --> 00:41:10,530
You get me?

593
00:41:11,239 --> 00:41:14,117
- I'll get dizzy?
- You'll spend your life drooling.

594
00:41:16,036 --> 00:41:17,037
No!

595
00:41:18,121 --> 00:41:20,123
Stay away. I said stay away,
you son of a bitch!

596
00:41:20,207 --> 00:41:22,000
Hey! You bastard!

597
00:41:22,084 --> 00:41:24,711
Stop it! Hey, don't do it!

598
00:41:26,713 --> 00:41:28,131
I almost died!

599
00:41:31,093 --> 00:41:32,344
Don't do it.

600
00:41:32,636 --> 00:41:34,221
Stop! You're not really going
to inject me, are you?

601
00:41:34,304 --> 00:41:35,639
I'll ask you one last time.

602
00:41:35,722 --> 00:41:37,015
This is driving me crazy.

603
00:41:37,349 --> 00:41:38,350
Who are you really?

604
00:41:38,433 --> 00:41:40,435
I just went because the fried dumplings
were delicious!

605
00:41:42,020 --> 00:41:43,563
The dumplings were delicious, you say?

606
00:41:43,939 --> 00:41:46,650
Those fried dumplings
you've been eating for ten years...

607
00:41:47,025 --> 00:41:50,028
are just factory-made
frozen dumplings, you idiot.

608
00:41:50,946 --> 00:41:53,573
Well, then I guess the frozen ones
must be really delicious.

609
00:41:53,657 --> 00:41:56,827
- This will sting a bit. Hang in there.
- Don't.

610
00:41:56,910 --> 00:41:58,161
Just bear with it.

611
00:41:58,245 --> 00:42:00,330
- Just bear with it. It's okay.
- Don't. Just...

612
00:42:00,580 --> 00:42:01,873
No, don't do it!

613
00:42:04,459 --> 00:42:06,044
Don't! Wait!

614
00:42:06,294 --> 00:42:07,504
Hwasan Sect!

615
00:42:07,587 --> 00:42:09,422
- Hwasan Sect!
- Hwasan Sect?

616
00:42:09,714 --> 00:42:11,758
The ones who were arrested
for murdering Director Kwon.

617
00:42:11,842 --> 00:42:12,884
Hwang Hwa-san's Hwasan Sect?

618
00:42:12,968 --> 00:42:14,136
That was a frame-up!

619
00:42:14,219 --> 00:42:16,680
We were framed by that bastard
Han Gyeong-wook too!

620
00:42:19,307 --> 00:42:21,226
Stop beating around the bush
and tell me straight.

621
00:42:21,309 --> 00:42:22,894
Ten years ago, when you were on the ferry

622
00:42:22,978 --> 00:42:24,229
I was there too.

623
00:42:31,069 --> 00:42:32,779
Han Gyeong-wook gave us an order

624
00:42:32,863 --> 00:42:34,114
to retrieve the package.

625
00:42:34,739 --> 00:42:36,783
So you were the one
who interfered that day?

626
00:42:36,867 --> 00:42:37,868
That's right!

627
00:42:38,368 --> 00:42:40,579
But things went south, seriously.

628
00:42:42,247 --> 00:42:45,542
We were supposed to intercept the package
that this "Bulgae" was after

629
00:42:46,543 --> 00:42:48,003
and use it to take down Han Gyeong-wook

630
00:42:48,086 --> 00:42:50,130
for what he did to our Chairman!

631
00:42:55,468 --> 00:42:56,511
We were...

632
00:42:56,970 --> 00:42:59,139
are victims of that bastard
Han Gyeong-wook.

633
00:42:59,931 --> 00:43:01,433
After that incident ten years ago

634
00:43:01,683 --> 00:43:03,226
do you have any idea
what happened to the Hwasan Sect?

635
00:43:03,476 --> 00:43:04,686
Watch out!

636
00:43:13,820 --> 00:43:14,821
Boss!

637
00:43:14,905 --> 00:43:15,906
Boss!

638
00:43:16,531 --> 00:43:18,658
Han Gyeong-wook...
He worked with Yoo In-gu

639
00:43:18,742 --> 00:43:20,660
and set me up.

640
00:43:21,203 --> 00:43:23,038
I guess this is the end
for the Hwasan Sect.

641
00:43:23,121 --> 00:43:24,414
It's not over yet!

642
00:43:25,207 --> 00:43:27,042
That National Intelligence Service agent
who got in our way...

643
00:43:27,792 --> 00:43:29,836
- He's on Yeongseon Island right now.
- Goodness...

644
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:30,921
- Yeongseon Island?
- Yes.

645
00:43:31,004 --> 00:43:33,256
The item that guy, Bulgae
or whatever, is looking for...

646
00:43:33,465 --> 00:43:34,799
We saw him go in to find it

647
00:43:34,883 --> 00:43:36,635
with our own two eyes, Boss.

648
00:43:36,718 --> 00:43:39,054
The item that Han Gyeong-wook
was so desperate to find...

649
00:43:39,137 --> 00:43:40,680
If we can just get our hands on it...

650
00:43:45,268 --> 00:43:46,478
You guys.

651
00:43:46,561 --> 00:43:49,856
Go back to Yeongseon Island
and find that item, understand?

652
00:43:50,607 --> 00:43:51,942
We'll meet again.

653
00:43:52,025 --> 00:43:54,069
Go. Go on.

654
00:43:55,570 --> 00:43:57,030
Hey! Get them now!

655
00:43:57,447 --> 00:43:59,115
- Hurry!
- Yes, sir.

656
00:44:00,867 --> 00:44:03,245
To clear our Boss's name...

657
00:44:03,578 --> 00:44:05,163
and rebuild the Hwasan Sect

658
00:44:05,497 --> 00:44:07,749
finding that item was our only hope.

659
00:44:10,085 --> 00:44:11,920
So, Jeong Ho-myeong.

660
00:44:12,796 --> 00:44:15,590
Since Jeong Ho-myeong
is the best agent in the NIS

661
00:44:16,049 --> 00:44:17,425
he'd find the item. Or rather...

662
00:44:18,093 --> 00:44:19,094
he'd find it for us.

663
00:44:22,222 --> 00:44:23,223
Damn it!

664
00:44:25,392 --> 00:44:26,393
Boss.

665
00:44:26,810 --> 00:44:28,270
It's been three months already.

666
00:44:28,520 --> 00:44:31,231
How long are we going to just sit here
and watch him fool around?

667
00:44:31,690 --> 00:44:34,609
If we jump the gun and screw up like
last time, are you gonna take the blame?

668
00:44:36,444 --> 00:44:37,988
He may not look like much

669
00:44:38,071 --> 00:44:40,323
but he's the top black ops agent
for the National Intelligence Service.

670
00:44:40,407 --> 00:44:42,993
There's a reason he went undercover
at that Chinese restaurant.

671
00:44:44,494 --> 00:44:46,579
All we have to do is jump him

672
00:44:46,663 --> 00:44:47,831
the moment he gets the item.

673
00:44:50,959 --> 00:44:52,961
Yeah, I just had to wait.

674
00:44:53,545 --> 00:44:57,173
That delivery guy must have
some grand plan to be acting like that.

675
00:44:57,632 --> 00:44:59,509
There's no way he's just sitting
on his hands for no reason.

676
00:45:00,176 --> 00:45:03,388
There must be a way to find the item...

677
00:45:04,139 --> 00:45:06,016
...at the restaurant.
That's why he's there.

678
00:45:06,808 --> 00:45:08,268
Every single day, 365 days a year

679
00:45:08,351 --> 00:45:11,271
I waited endlessly, praying and praying.

680
00:45:11,354 --> 00:45:13,356
Praying that Jeong Ho-myeong
would finally make his move.

681
00:45:13,440 --> 00:45:15,442
Praying for a way out of this hell.

682
00:45:16,776 --> 00:45:17,819
But you...

683
00:45:18,486 --> 00:45:21,698
you were too busy playing house
with the\ restaurant owner's daughter.

684
00:45:21,781 --> 00:45:23,241
You didn't seem to care
about finding the item at all.

685
00:45:23,325 --> 00:45:24,784
You looked so happy, didn't you?

686
00:45:24,868 --> 00:45:26,661
CONVENIENCE STORE FOR FREE NO KEY MONEY
PLEASE, JUST TAKE OVER

687
00:45:27,704 --> 00:45:29,748
You think I wanted to start working
at a convenience store?

688
00:45:30,665 --> 00:45:32,625
I had to do something to get by.

689
00:45:32,709 --> 00:45:33,877
This is all...

690
00:45:34,419 --> 00:45:35,920
your fault, Jeong Ho-myeong!

691
00:45:44,721 --> 00:45:48,141
- Is he crazy?
- What a load of crap.

692
00:45:48,266 --> 00:45:49,934
Still, that doesn't make sense.
For ten years...

693
00:45:50,435 --> 00:45:52,437
- So gangsters ran a convenience store?
- What about you?

694
00:45:52,729 --> 00:45:54,064
The so-called top agent at the NIS

695
00:45:54,147 --> 00:45:56,024
- is running a Chinese restaurant?
- What?

696
00:45:56,149 --> 00:45:57,317
And how was I supposed to know

697
00:45:57,400 --> 00:45:59,069
I'd be stuck as a convenience store clerk
for ten years?

698
00:45:59,402 --> 00:46:01,738
Jeong Ho-myeong,
you're supposed to be the NIS's top agent.

699
00:46:02,072 --> 00:46:04,616
None of this would've happened
if you'd just found the item in time!

700
00:46:04,699 --> 00:46:05,700
You son of a bitch.

701
00:46:05,784 --> 00:46:07,077
Are you blaming me for this?

702
00:46:07,243 --> 00:46:08,453
You think I enjoyed living like this?

703
00:46:08,536 --> 00:46:09,579
-You seemed to be enjoying it.

704
00:46:09,662 --> 00:46:12,290
Marrying into the family
of a popular restaurant, having a kid...

705
00:46:12,374 --> 00:46:13,666
you looked plenty happy to me.

706
00:46:13,750 --> 00:46:16,628
A lot happier than me,
working 12-hour shifts.

707
00:46:16,711 --> 00:46:17,712
Am I wrong?

708
00:46:18,755 --> 00:46:21,007
You little punk. So you were born in 1992?

709
00:46:21,091 --> 00:46:23,134
- Why'd you hit me?
- Show some respect.

710
00:46:24,594 --> 00:46:26,012
Help me.

711
00:46:31,476 --> 00:46:32,477
Please help me.

712
00:46:32,560 --> 00:46:33,603
I'm begging you!

713
00:46:50,036 --> 00:46:51,579
When I think about how you guys

714
00:46:51,663 --> 00:46:52,831
botched the operation ten years ago...

715
00:46:52,914 --> 00:46:54,833
I still want to tear you limb from limb.

716
00:46:55,041 --> 00:46:56,209
But what's the point of going after

717
00:46:56,292 --> 00:46:58,920
a worthless small fry like you now?

718
00:46:59,421 --> 00:47:01,423
I'd rather use you as bait...

719
00:47:02,257 --> 00:47:03,716
to land a bigger fish.

720
00:47:03,967 --> 00:47:05,135
What? Bait?

721
00:47:05,468 --> 00:47:07,011
From now on, you'll do exactly as I say.

722
00:47:07,095 --> 00:47:09,180
What, am I crazy?

723
00:47:09,764 --> 00:47:12,225
Just do it. Quit giving me lip, you punk.

724
00:47:13,476 --> 00:47:14,727
Ugh, seriously.

725
00:47:15,812 --> 00:47:16,813
Sit.

726
00:47:17,689 --> 00:47:18,731
I said, sit!

727
00:47:18,857 --> 00:47:19,858
Good grief.

728
00:47:24,279 --> 00:47:27,031
The two men who were captured
with you yesterday...

729
00:47:28,116 --> 00:47:29,868
The one with the messed-up face...

730
00:47:30,994 --> 00:47:32,829
- is Bulgae.
- What? Bulgae?

731
00:47:33,329 --> 00:47:35,540
Him? Then what about the package?
Did you find it?

732
00:47:35,623 --> 00:47:36,624
No.

733
00:47:36,749 --> 00:47:38,460
You're going to find it. Starting now.

734
00:47:39,377 --> 00:47:41,713
Tail Bulgae and find that package,
one way or another.

735
00:47:42,797 --> 00:47:44,299
Are you out of your mind?

736
00:47:44,841 --> 00:47:45,884
You think I'm actually going to do that?

737
00:47:46,134 --> 00:47:47,218
Be your lackey?

738
00:47:49,345 --> 00:47:50,346
Is that right?

739
00:47:52,724 --> 00:47:54,309
I wonder if you'll still refuse
after seeing this.

740
00:47:58,897 --> 00:48:00,356
Oh, hell.

741
00:48:04,277 --> 00:48:05,320
This video...

742
00:48:05,528 --> 00:48:08,072
How about I send it to every gangster
in every group chat?

743
00:48:08,573 --> 00:48:10,742
No, please. Please, I'm begging you.

744
00:48:11,159 --> 00:48:12,160
Please, just don't do that.

745
00:48:12,243 --> 00:48:14,078
- Then you'll do as I say.
- Okay.

746
00:48:14,621 --> 00:48:18,166
Do that, and I'll pave the way for you
to get your revenge.

747
00:48:19,501 --> 00:48:22,128
Because I have a score
to settle with them too.

748
00:48:28,676 --> 00:48:30,136
I'm the only one who will call you

749
00:48:30,220 --> 00:48:31,846
so answer within exactly ten seconds.

750
00:48:32,013 --> 00:48:33,139
If you're even one second late...

751
00:48:34,224 --> 00:48:35,225
you know what'll happen.

752
00:48:47,779 --> 00:48:49,113
Nam-il, you done packing?

753
00:48:50,865 --> 00:48:51,991
What is this, a midnight run?

754
00:48:52,075 --> 00:48:53,826
Why are we suddenly packing?

755
00:48:53,952 --> 00:48:55,703
You want to get dragged away
and beaten half to death again?

756
00:48:56,246 --> 00:48:57,956
Less talking, more packing.

757
00:48:58,039 --> 00:48:59,165
They may have said three days...

758
00:48:59,249 --> 00:49:01,251
but who knows when those guys
will show up again.

759
00:49:01,334 --> 00:49:02,335
And where are we supposed to go?

760
00:49:02,418 --> 00:49:04,379
You don't have any money or friends.

761
00:49:08,883 --> 00:49:09,884
Hey!

762
00:49:11,719 --> 00:49:13,638
You wouldn't know,
but plenty of people would take me in.

763
00:49:14,222 --> 00:49:15,848
Fine, then go to one of those places.

764
00:49:16,474 --> 00:49:17,475
I'll just stay with my friends.

765
00:49:17,559 --> 00:49:19,435
You lost our house running around
with those damn friends

766
00:49:19,519 --> 00:49:20,520
and you want to go to them?

767
00:49:21,145 --> 00:49:22,397
Stop talking nonsense and just pack.

768
00:49:22,480 --> 00:49:24,941
Come on, we have to go
before it gets any later.

769
00:49:29,362 --> 00:49:30,363
So...

770
00:49:31,114 --> 00:49:32,115
where are we going, then?

771
00:49:43,960 --> 00:49:44,961
We're here.

772
00:49:51,884 --> 00:49:52,885
Put our stuff over here.

773
00:49:52,969 --> 00:49:54,804
That way, people can walk by
and not even notice.

774
00:49:58,099 --> 00:50:01,561
The only place you could find
was a closet in the company cafeteria?

775
00:50:01,644 --> 00:50:02,979
What?

776
00:50:03,062 --> 00:50:04,647
It's nice and cozy.

777
00:50:05,273 --> 00:50:06,357
If you take a nap here

778
00:50:06,441 --> 00:50:07,483
you'll sleep like a log.

779
00:50:12,238 --> 00:50:14,782
What are we, parasites?

780
00:50:15,033 --> 00:50:16,784
We should've just gotten a motel.

781
00:50:18,536 --> 00:50:19,996
Stop being so spoiled.

782
00:50:20,330 --> 00:50:21,831
We have to save every last penny

783
00:50:21,914 --> 00:50:23,541
if we want to get our house back.

784
00:50:26,544 --> 00:50:27,545
But if we get caught

785
00:50:27,629 --> 00:50:29,005
aren't you going to get fired?

786
00:50:29,797 --> 00:50:31,466
What's the difference
between clocking in tomorrow

787
00:50:31,549 --> 00:50:33,051
and just coming in a little early today?

788
00:50:33,176 --> 00:50:34,510
Stop whining

789
00:50:34,594 --> 00:50:35,678
and just get inside.

790
00:51:11,631 --> 00:51:13,758
- The ingredients for today are prepped.
- Okay.

791
00:51:13,966 --> 00:51:15,593
- I'll leave the lunch service to you.
- What?

792
00:51:15,677 --> 00:51:17,679
To me? Hey, wait.

793
00:51:17,762 --> 00:51:20,390
First, we have two targets to keep an eye
on.

794
00:51:20,723 --> 00:51:23,226
First, there's Yoo In-gu,
Han Gyeong-wook's right-hand man.

795
00:51:23,851 --> 00:51:25,603
Currently the boss of the Ingu Sect

796
00:51:25,687 --> 00:51:27,230
and the president of Heaven Capital.

797
00:51:27,647 --> 00:51:29,399
There's a reason he's running
his loan shark business

798
00:51:29,482 --> 00:51:31,359
specifically on Yeongseon Island.

799
00:51:32,068 --> 00:51:35,113
I'm going to dig into his background
and figure out his goal.

800
00:51:35,488 --> 00:51:36,781
Next up, Bulgae.

801
00:51:36,864 --> 00:51:38,324
Former North Korean special agent.

802
00:51:38,408 --> 00:51:40,201
His current alias is Bong Je-sun.

803
00:51:40,284 --> 00:51:41,869
According to our intel,
for the past ten years

804
00:51:41,953 --> 00:51:42,995
he's been living on Yeongseon Island

805
00:51:43,079 --> 00:51:45,081
with Heo Bong-pil
and his grandson, Nam-il.

806
00:51:45,415 --> 00:51:46,749
Heo Bong-pil has since passed away

807
00:51:46,833 --> 00:51:49,210
and now he lives alone with Nam-il,
a high school student.

808
00:51:49,544 --> 00:51:50,837
Currently...

809
00:51:51,087 --> 00:51:54,507
he's a manager at Yeongseon Steel,
a rebar processing plant.

810
00:51:55,049 --> 00:51:56,259
This guy...

811
00:51:56,342 --> 00:51:58,052
Ma Gong-bok, you're good at
digging into people's pasts.

812
00:51:58,136 --> 00:51:59,220
You'll take this one.

813
00:52:00,722 --> 00:52:01,723
Oh, man.

814
00:52:01,806 --> 00:52:04,559
He tells people he has amnesia

815
00:52:04,642 --> 00:52:06,602
but it's highly likely just an act.

816
00:52:07,311 --> 00:52:09,355
Thoroughly figure out his true intentions

817
00:52:09,439 --> 00:52:12,150
and finding the item is our objective.

818
00:52:12,650 --> 00:52:16,028
Oh, please. Please, just leave it. Please!

819
00:52:18,030 --> 00:52:22,618
No. Oh, come on.

820
00:52:26,497 --> 00:52:28,624
If you need anything, just give me a call.

821
00:52:33,379 --> 00:52:34,714
- Gong-bok.
- Oh, you're back?

822
00:52:34,797 --> 00:52:37,133
- I ran the numbers.
- Right. Thanks for your hard work.

823
00:52:38,342 --> 00:52:40,011
We're short exactly 300 won!

824
00:52:46,809 --> 00:52:47,810
YEONGSEON FOOD

825
00:52:48,853 --> 00:52:50,146
Boss, I'm dragging her with me.

826
00:52:51,272 --> 00:52:52,273
Honey!

827
00:52:53,232 --> 00:52:54,901
Let's do this in one go, huh?

828
00:52:55,067 --> 00:52:56,235
I'm sorry.

829
00:52:57,570 --> 00:52:58,905
Out of the way.

830
00:53:00,698 --> 00:53:03,075
Stop struggling, damn it. Good.

831
00:53:03,159 --> 00:53:04,452
That's it.

832
00:53:11,083 --> 00:53:12,627
So, these guys

833
00:53:12,710 --> 00:53:15,087
are threatening people who have gambling
debts and took out loans

834
00:53:15,171 --> 00:53:17,590
and buying up all the land
they can on Yeongseon Island.

835
00:53:19,050 --> 00:53:20,051
Hey, thug.

836
00:53:20,134 --> 00:53:23,429
You must have a reason
for extorting people like this, right?

837
00:53:24,013 --> 00:53:25,681
- Spit it out.
- Oh, come on.

838
00:53:26,224 --> 00:53:28,392
Don't lump us in with scum like Yoo In-gu.

839
00:53:28,476 --> 00:53:29,811
Our main business was nightlife.

840
00:53:29,936 --> 00:53:31,813
We never got our hands dirty
with business like this.

841
00:53:31,896 --> 00:53:33,606
So what if your business was different?

842
00:53:33,689 --> 00:53:35,233
You were still thugs,
so you must know something.

843
00:53:35,316 --> 00:53:36,400
Can't you tell just by looking?

844
00:53:36,692 --> 00:53:39,487
It's a classic property holdout scheme
you see in redevelopment zones.

845
00:53:39,570 --> 00:53:41,864
They snatch up cheap land
for next to nothing

846
00:53:41,989 --> 00:53:43,324
and once it's designated a
redevelopment zone

847
00:53:43,407 --> 00:53:45,827
they sell high and cash out.
A classic holdout.

848
00:53:46,077 --> 00:53:47,620
So you're saying
what these guys are doing is

849
00:53:47,703 --> 00:53:49,705
just a simple redevelopment scheme?

850
00:53:49,789 --> 00:53:51,123
Well...

851
00:53:51,499 --> 00:53:53,167
but something about it does seem fishy,
right?

852
00:53:53,793 --> 00:53:55,336
I mean, if it were land
in Gangnam, Seoul, I'd get it.

853
00:53:55,419 --> 00:53:58,172
But how much can land on Yeongseon Island
be worth? Why go through the trouble?

854
00:53:58,256 --> 00:53:59,632
There doesn't seem
to be much profit in it.

855
00:54:00,299 --> 00:54:02,009
Han Gyeong-wook's main campaign promise is

856
00:54:02,093 --> 00:54:04,178
the large-scale development of Yeongseon
Island.

857
00:54:04,512 --> 00:54:06,639
[They're just trying to get a piece of the
development project.

858
00:54:08,057 --> 00:54:10,017
Aren't they just barking up
the wrong tree?

859
00:54:11,561 --> 00:54:13,938
Do you even know who Han Gyeong-wook is?
How can you say that?

860
00:54:14,522 --> 00:54:17,441
You think he's starting this development
project just to improve Yeongseon Island?

861
00:54:17,525 --> 00:54:18,818
Actually, I don't know.

862
00:54:21,237 --> 00:54:22,864
Right. Anyway, what about Bulgae?

863
00:54:36,002 --> 00:54:37,879
What is this? Jeez.

864
00:54:37,962 --> 00:54:40,047
Who told you to take these pictures? Huh?

865
00:54:40,131 --> 00:54:41,966
What is this? Him eating ramyun?

866
00:54:42,508 --> 00:54:43,718
Why would you take a picture of this?

867
00:54:43,801 --> 00:54:46,637
He's cooped up at the company 24/7.
What do you expect me to do?

868
00:54:47,263 --> 00:54:48,556
After Yoo In-gu took his house

869
00:54:48,639 --> 00:54:50,516
he started hiding out
and living at the company.

870
00:54:50,766 --> 00:54:52,393
He never leaves the office.

871
00:54:53,144 --> 00:54:54,729
Hey, you.

872
00:54:54,812 --> 00:54:58,649
Hey, look at this. Huh?
I have this video scheduled to...

873
00:55:01,861 --> 00:55:03,863
I did everything you asked,
but this is going too far!

874
00:55:03,946 --> 00:55:06,282
That only applies if you actually
put some effort into your investigation.

875
00:55:06,699 --> 00:55:08,451
If you come back with nothing next time,
this video is going straight

876
00:55:08,534 --> 00:55:09,869
to NewTube. Got it?

877
00:55:13,247 --> 00:55:14,749
Do we really have to do this here?

878
00:55:14,832 --> 00:55:17,710
I'm practically a pro at giving baths.
Now, come on.

879
00:55:28,179 --> 00:55:29,472
No way.

880
00:55:29,555 --> 00:55:30,806
You go wash up.

881
00:55:30,890 --> 00:55:34,727
You stink. Your whole body stinks,
you hear me?

882
00:55:34,810 --> 00:55:36,938
I can't sleep because of you.
You smell like crap.

883
00:55:37,021 --> 00:55:38,064
What smell?

884
00:55:38,147 --> 00:55:39,899
I showered just last week!

885
00:55:43,277 --> 00:55:44,278
Bend over.

886
00:55:56,499 --> 00:55:58,376
What are you two doing in here?

887
00:56:03,172 --> 00:56:06,217
So, because of your
nephew's gambling debts

888
00:56:06,300 --> 00:56:08,344
you lost your house to Heaven Capital

889
00:56:08,719 --> 00:56:10,179
and with nowhere to go

890
00:56:10,471 --> 00:56:12,473
you've been hiding out here
at the company?

891
00:56:14,558 --> 00:56:16,602
What were you thinking? Seriously.

892
00:56:16,894 --> 00:56:19,438
Are you trying to find a creative way
to get fired or something?

893
00:56:20,648 --> 00:56:21,649
Manager Lee.

894
00:56:23,651 --> 00:56:24,777
Please, just cut me some slack.

895
00:56:25,778 --> 00:56:27,530
I wouldn't be doing this
if I wasn't desperate.

896
00:56:27,989 --> 00:56:28,990
Just for a little while.

897
00:56:29,907 --> 00:56:31,993
Just until I have enough money
for a new place, okay?

898
00:56:32,076 --> 00:56:33,369
And what if I get in trouble?

899
00:56:40,251 --> 00:56:42,294
If you get caught,
I don't know anything about this.

900
00:56:44,380 --> 00:56:45,631
Manager Lee.

901
00:56:46,173 --> 00:56:50,011
I'll handle it, no matter what.
Manager Lee, thank you so much.

902
00:57:01,063 --> 00:57:02,440
Did you get the exact amount?

903
00:57:02,523 --> 00:57:04,191
Yes, I just barely managed it.

904
00:57:05,985 --> 00:57:07,028
But, boss...

905
00:57:08,029 --> 00:57:09,488
Are you sure about this?

906
00:57:10,281 --> 00:57:12,199
All the money from Heaven Capital
and the Ingu Sect's funds

907
00:57:12,283 --> 00:57:14,035
are in here...

908
00:57:14,910 --> 00:57:18,164
If this goes south, we'll immediately
run out of money for our loans, boss.

909
00:57:18,289 --> 00:57:20,916
Jeez, you have no guts.

910
00:57:21,709 --> 00:57:23,210
Ever heard of high risk, high return?

911
00:57:24,128 --> 00:57:27,006
If this deal goes well, we'll get back ten
times our investment, and then some.

912
00:57:27,965 --> 00:57:31,844
Just you watch and learn
how I built up the Ingu Sect.

913
00:57:32,678 --> 00:57:34,305
- Welcome, boss!
- Yeah.

914
00:57:36,474 --> 00:57:37,475
Boss.

915
00:57:37,975 --> 00:57:40,186
- Where are the Chinese guys?
- They're waiting inside.

916
00:58:00,831 --> 00:58:03,417
President Yoo, you don't disappoint.

917
00:58:03,793 --> 00:58:05,753
You really get things done.

918
00:58:07,963 --> 00:58:09,381
Those guys from the Mainland are so picky

919
00:58:09,590 --> 00:58:11,133
it was a real pain sealing the deal.

920
00:58:14,428 --> 00:58:16,472
- What about the rest of the shipment?
- They're busting their asses making it

921
00:58:16,555 --> 00:58:18,057
because the order's so big.

922
00:58:18,432 --> 00:58:20,643
They'll bring the rest
on the next delivery date.

923
00:58:20,893 --> 00:58:23,437
People in Gangnam
will go crazy for quality like this.

924
00:58:23,521 --> 00:58:25,064
Forget Gangnam.

925
00:58:25,147 --> 00:58:27,525
Now, all the Ingu Sect has to do
is rake in the cash.

926
00:58:28,734 --> 00:58:30,069
All right, good work, President Choi.

927
00:58:30,986 --> 00:58:34,448
Make sure the Mainland guys
know we're off to a great start.

928
00:58:34,573 --> 00:58:36,200
This isn't some mom-and-pop shop.

929
00:58:36,283 --> 00:58:38,119
It's the best drug production line
on the Mainland.

930
00:58:38,202 --> 00:58:40,454
No need to worry, those guys are pros
when it comes to business.

931
00:58:40,538 --> 00:58:42,373
All you need to worry about
is the deal date.

932
00:58:43,457 --> 00:58:45,417
He worries about such useless things.

933
00:58:45,501 --> 00:58:47,795
Something's off. It smells fishy.

934
00:58:48,546 --> 00:58:50,214
Come on, think about it.

935
00:58:50,297 --> 00:58:53,050
What they're doing at the capital firm is
shady enough

936
00:58:53,134 --> 00:58:54,718
but running a jerky factory?

937
00:58:56,220 --> 00:58:58,264
What the hell are they up to?

938
00:58:59,181 --> 00:59:01,100
Hey, isn't the jerky factory just a front?

939
00:59:01,684 --> 00:59:02,977
To drag people there
and beat the crap out of them?

940
00:59:03,060 --> 00:59:04,728
No, I thought so too

941
00:59:04,812 --> 00:59:06,605
but they're actually producing jerky.

942
00:59:06,814 --> 00:59:08,524
Hey, that guy, Yoo In-gu,
took over the Hwasan Sect

943
00:59:08,607 --> 00:59:10,401
and joined forces
with Han Gyeong-wook, right?

944
00:59:11,068 --> 00:59:12,111
Then he must be

945
00:59:12,194 --> 00:59:13,988
acting on Han Gyeong-wook's orders.

946
00:59:15,406 --> 00:59:19,243
What the hell are they doing
on Yeongseon Island? Damn it.

947
00:59:19,577 --> 00:59:21,078
What about that other guy
from the Hwasan Sect?

948
00:59:21,495 --> 00:59:23,622
That Ma Gong-bok guy, is he of any use?

949
00:59:23,706 --> 00:59:25,791
I'm just using him
because I'm short-handed.

950
00:59:25,875 --> 00:59:28,252
I mean, can you really trust
some washed-up gangster?

951
00:59:30,296 --> 00:59:32,673
First Bulgae, and now Yoo In-gu...

952
00:59:33,299 --> 00:59:34,425
Whatever's going on

953
00:59:34,508 --> 00:59:35,801
I need to put an end to it.

954
00:59:36,010 --> 00:59:37,011
Put an end to it?

955
00:59:39,555 --> 00:59:41,015
What are you thinking?

956
00:59:43,434 --> 00:59:44,643
I have a bad feeling about this.

957
00:59:45,019 --> 00:59:46,812
I think it's about time I made a move.

958
00:59:46,979 --> 00:59:48,856
No, no. You can't.

959
00:59:48,939 --> 00:59:50,524
Things are still too uncertain.

960
00:59:50,608 --> 00:59:53,068
Let's move when we have a clearer picture.

961
00:59:53,152 --> 00:59:55,070
No. There's no point in waiting.

962
00:59:55,571 --> 00:59:56,947
What are you going to do then?

963
00:59:57,114 --> 00:59:58,324
I guess...

964
00:59:59,116 --> 01:00:00,284
with Yoo In-gu...

965
01:00:00,784 --> 01:00:02,119
I'll have to have a little chat.

966
01:00:02,328 --> 01:00:03,329
A talk?

967
01:00:03,621 --> 01:00:04,622
By yourself?

968
01:00:05,247 --> 01:00:06,832
When have I ever needed backup?

969
01:00:10,211 --> 01:00:12,880
Wow, look at how pure and white this is.

970
01:00:12,963 --> 01:00:16,258
Whoa, this is definitely
top-shelf, boss. Right?

971
01:00:16,383 --> 01:00:17,384
Hey.

972
01:00:17,468 --> 01:00:20,930
If we get stuff of this quality
on the next deal

973
01:00:21,013 --> 01:00:22,932
it'll sell like hotcakes

974
01:00:23,390 --> 01:00:25,476
and the money
will come rolling in like crazy.

975
01:00:25,684 --> 01:00:29,230
Then all this cleaning up
Chief Han's messes...

976
01:00:29,313 --> 01:00:31,398
and groveling will finally be over.

977
01:00:31,482 --> 01:00:32,650
That's right, boss.

978
01:00:33,484 --> 01:00:34,485
- Kang-sik.
- Yes.

979
01:00:34,902 --> 01:00:37,238
Today's deal went well,
so let's go somewhere nice for a change.

980
01:00:41,951 --> 01:00:44,328
I'm gonna go take a leak
so everyone get ready.

981
01:00:44,411 --> 01:00:45,412
Yes, sir.

982
01:00:51,961 --> 01:00:53,462
- Yes, sir.
- Yeah.

983
01:01:19,697 --> 01:01:21,907
Sounds like you're having some trouble.

984
01:01:22,449 --> 01:01:24,576
I know a good doctor for prostate issues.

985
01:01:24,743 --> 01:01:25,744
So...

986
01:01:26,245 --> 01:01:27,913
want a referral?

987
01:01:29,081 --> 01:01:30,082
Yoo In-gu?

988
01:01:32,293 --> 01:01:33,419
Who the hell are you?

989
01:01:51,145 --> 01:01:52,563
I got piss all over me.

990
01:01:52,980 --> 01:01:54,023
You're dead.

991
01:02:02,239 --> 01:02:04,074
Who the hell are you? Who sent you?

992
01:02:04,158 --> 01:02:05,659
Can't you tell?

993
01:02:05,743 --> 01:02:07,286
I'm the Masked Racer.

994
01:02:08,454 --> 01:02:10,247
I'm here to punish scumbags like you.

995
01:02:10,706 --> 01:02:12,583
The Masked Racer!

996
01:02:14,710 --> 01:02:17,254
Damn psycho. Is he out of his mind?

997
01:02:18,589 --> 01:02:20,674
You see, for the past few days

998
01:02:20,758 --> 01:02:23,385
I've been watching all the shit
you've been pulling.

999
01:02:23,844 --> 01:02:26,889
And there's something
I just can't seem to wrap my head around.

1000
01:02:27,139 --> 01:02:28,140
So I want to ask you a few questions.

1001
01:02:28,223 --> 01:02:30,351
You bastard! Do you have any idea what
you're getting yourself into?

1002
01:02:40,152 --> 01:02:41,153
Tell me.

1003
01:02:41,612 --> 01:02:43,906
Why you gangster bastards
from the Ingu Sect...

1004
01:02:43,989 --> 01:02:46,075
are running rampant on Yeongseon Island.

1005
01:02:46,533 --> 01:02:49,453
Why are you threatening people
and stealing their homes and land?

1006
01:02:50,329 --> 01:02:53,290
Damn it. You sure are curious...

1007
01:03:07,012 --> 01:03:08,305
Believe it or not

1008
01:03:08,389 --> 01:03:10,307
I'm a humanitarian.

1009
01:03:10,849 --> 01:03:13,227
And just beating you senseless
isn't my style.

1010
01:03:17,106 --> 01:03:18,607
What are you waiting for? Grab it.

1011
01:03:23,028 --> 01:03:25,072
You're dead, you bastard.

1012
01:03:25,572 --> 01:03:26,824
Jeez.

1013
01:03:30,828 --> 01:03:31,829
I think...

1014
01:03:32,830 --> 01:03:35,582
Boss has been gone for a while,
don't you think?

1015
01:03:37,126 --> 01:03:38,293
Should I go check on him?

1016
01:03:41,505 --> 01:03:42,840
This little punk.

1017
01:03:43,841 --> 01:03:46,343
How dare you?
The Boss is taking care of his business.

1018
01:04:00,441 --> 01:04:02,276
I'll ask you one last time.

1019
01:04:02,359 --> 01:04:04,278
What's your purpose on Yeongseon Island?

1020
01:04:04,361 --> 01:04:06,905
I don't know, you psycho bastard!

1021
01:04:16,123 --> 01:04:20,127
You. Do you know
when people are the most truthful?

1022
01:04:21,044 --> 01:04:22,838
It's when they're in pain.

1023
01:04:23,922 --> 01:04:26,341
Okay, I'll talk! I said I'll talk.

1024
01:04:29,261 --> 01:04:30,387
We...

1025
01:04:32,014 --> 01:04:34,475
Our purpose on Yeongseon Island is...

1026
01:04:37,394 --> 01:04:38,520
Screw off.

1027
01:04:53,160 --> 01:04:54,161
What the...

1028
01:04:55,871 --> 01:04:57,331
Damn it.

1029
01:05:05,506 --> 01:05:07,174
Damn it, pick up the phone faster!

1030
01:05:10,802 --> 01:05:12,429
- Yes, Boss.
- Hey, Kang-sik!

1031
01:05:12,721 --> 01:05:14,932
-Yes, Boss.
-Kang-sik, the bathroom, now!

1032
01:05:15,015 --> 01:05:17,017
- Yes, Boss?
- Get your ass to the bathroom, damn it!

1033
01:05:17,434 --> 01:05:19,102
You useless punk, the bathroom!

1034
01:05:20,312 --> 01:05:21,480
Hey, to the bathroom!

1035
01:05:22,272 --> 01:05:24,233
Get to the bathroom, you bastards! Move!

1036
01:05:24,316 --> 01:05:25,984
Yes, sir.

1037
01:05:33,992 --> 01:05:35,619
I know who you are.

1038
01:05:35,702 --> 01:05:37,621
You're that guy whose land I took, right?

1039
01:05:37,704 --> 01:05:39,498
Huh? The Martial Arts Master, right?

1040
01:05:40,666 --> 01:05:42,042
I'm the one asking questions here.

1041
01:05:42,125 --> 01:05:43,919
What is your purpose?

1042
01:05:50,551 --> 01:05:52,344
Hey, you so-called Martial Arts Master.

1043
01:05:52,427 --> 01:05:53,637
You think you're going
to walk away from this? Huh?

1044
01:05:57,558 --> 01:05:58,642
Boss!

1045
01:06:01,395 --> 01:06:02,938
Boss!

1046
01:06:06,608 --> 01:06:07,609
What is that?

1047
01:06:08,360 --> 01:06:09,570
What, does he think he's the hero?

1048
01:06:10,862 --> 01:06:13,782
Hey, you masked bastard.
Now you're dead meat.

1049
01:06:23,542 --> 01:06:26,211
SPECIAL THANKS TO KIM SANG-KYUNG
AND KWON YUL FOR THEIR APPEARANCE

1050
01:06:26,962 --> 01:06:29,339
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

1051
01:06:40,851 --> 01:06:42,769
One guy turned the
almighty Ingu Sect upside down?

1052
01:06:42,853 --> 01:06:44,187
He doesn't seem to be an ordinary man.

1053
01:06:45,439 --> 01:06:46,440
Get that masked bastard.

1054
01:06:46,523 --> 01:06:48,275
I said get him!

1055
01:06:48,358 --> 01:06:49,610
Guys, let's go!

1056
01:06:49,693 --> 01:06:52,154
The thugs are here to get you!

1057
01:06:52,362 --> 01:06:54,323
- Hey, get him! Quick!
- Yeongseon Food?

1058
01:06:54,406 --> 01:06:55,824
Let's recruit a gatekeeper.

1059
01:06:55,907 --> 01:06:57,242
Yeah, you bet I'm in.

1060
01:06:57,326 --> 01:06:59,911
- What do you need me to do?
- The Passenger Ship Spy Case.

1061
01:06:59,995 --> 01:07:01,830
- You know who this is, don't you?
- A prosecutor is here!

1062
01:07:01,913 --> 01:07:03,457
- A prosecutor!
- Should we take care of him?

1063
01:07:03,582 --> 01:07:04,875
Give me a call.

1064
01:07:04,958 --> 01:07:06,543
Let's wrap this up.

1065
01:07:06,627 --> 01:07:08,086
I was on that passenger ship.

1066
01:07:08,170 --> 01:07:10,088
If we just do nothing, you're really going
to die, Prosecutor Gang.

1067
01:07:10,172 --> 01:07:11,923
So I need to get moving?

1068
01:07:12,007 --> 01:07:13,050
For the sake of my family

1069
01:07:13,133 --> 01:07:14,676
there's nothing I wouldn't do.
